Not really; it might be correct if we say `((integer|string)[][]|nil)[]`, which is however confusing. The key (pattern_id) comes from the (1-based) index, in the order they appear in a query file, but they are not necessarily contiguous because some of them may not have predicates/directives. E.g.:

```lua
=vim.treesitter.query.get('c', 'locals').info
{
  captures = { "definition.function", "definition.macro", "scope", "definition.var", "definition.parameter", "definition.type", "definition.field", "definition", "reference" },
  patterns = {
    [15] = { { "set!", "reference.kind", "field" } },
    [16] = { { "set!", "reference.kind", "type" } }
  }
}
```
I will improve the documentation about the meaning of keys and values to be even clearer.
